Davis catapulted to national stardom back in June of 2013 after her eleven-hour filibuster temporarily delayed passage of Senate Bill 5, which contained sweeping new abortion restrictions in the state of Texas.

Despite her efforts, the Bill was eventually signed into law on July 18, 2013.

At one point during the filibuster, Davis said she almost felt compelled to talk about her failed pregnancies, but said she knew it would overshadow her effort to block the bill. 

